hackathon-description-text: Kent Hack Enough, HacKSU's annual hackathon, brings the passion and innovation behind hackathons to the Midwest. With over 300 participants, Kent Hack Enough will be the largest hackathon in Ohio. Top prizes will include cash and exposure to top companies. Admission is completely free for students, and travel costs will be reimbursed.
hackathon-eligibility:
- Undergraduate or graduate students at any college or university
 - High school students
 - Teams limited to 4 people
hackathon-requirements: Any software or hardware hacks are allowed!
hackathon-rules: In order to participate you must be a undergraduate or graduate student at a college or university. Contact us if you're a high school student wanting to participate. Projects must be started from scratch, but the use of 3rd party libraries and APIs is allowed. Team sizes are limited to 4 people.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Plus a 3 month trial on Codeship and Dell tablets for each team member.
A Leap Motion controller for each team member.
